## Error Response Handling

### Strapi Error Response Structure

```typescript
interface IStrapiResponse {
  ok: boolean;
  status: number;
  error: {
    message: string;
  };
  data: {
    id: number;
  } | null;
}
```

### Error Logging for API Calls

```typescript
if (!response.ok || result.error) {
  const errorMessage = result.error?.message ||
    `HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`;

  // Log to CSV file
  await writeDataToCSV(
    `"${id}","${errorMessage.replace(/"/g, '""')}"`,
    `strapi/logs/error-api-${this.currentTime}.csv`,
  );

  console.error(`❌ API call failed:`, errorMessage);
  throw new Error(errorMessage);
}
```

## Rate Limiting and Performance

### Chunked API Operations

```typescript
const chunkSize = 1; // Small chunks for API operations
for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i += chunkSize) {
  const chunk = data.slice(i, i + chunkSize);
  const promises = chunk.map((item) => this.apiCall(item));

  await Promise.all(promises);

  // Add delay between chunks
  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
}
```

### Retry Logic for API Calls

```typescript
public async apiCallWithRetry(
  operation: () => Promise<any>,
  maxRetries = 3
): Promise<any> {
  for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= maxRetries; attempt++) {
    try {
      return await operation();
    } catch (error) {
      if (attempt === maxRetries) {
        throw error;
      }
      
      console.log(`⚠️ API call failed, retrying... (${attempt}/${maxRetries})`);
      await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 1000 * attempt));
    }
  }
}
```

## Response Data Transformation

### Strapi Response Processing

```typescript
// Transform Strapi response to internal format
const transformedData = result.data.map((item: IStrapiForm) => {
  const { attributes } = item;

  return {
    id: item.id,
    title: attributes.title,
    slug: attributes.slug,
    categories: attributes.categories.data.map((cat) => ({
      id: cat.id,
      ...cat.attributes,
      parent: cat.attributes.parent?.data?.id,
    })),
    // ... other transformations
  };
});
```

### Nested Data Handling

```typescript
// Handle Strapi's nested data structure
const categoriesData = categories.data.map(({ id, attributes }) => {
  const { parent } = attributes;
  return {
    id,
    ...attributes,
    parent: parent?.data?.id,
  };
});
```
